1. I used ubuntu command line on windows subsystem for linux to run the yolov4;

2. Steps are: 1>enable windows subsystem for linux;
              2>download ubuntu 18.04 LTS from microsoft store;
              3>launch ubuntu 18.04 LTS;
              4>install necessary packages, including cmake, opencv, g++, omp, x11-xserver-utils, build-essential;
              5>download Xming X Server, it will let me display the output images or videos from ubuntu;
              6>run the Xming;
              7>enable the display in ubuntu command:
                    "export DISPLAY=:0"
                    "DIDSPLAY=:0 command"
              8>download darknet-master from github and extract it, download yolov4.cfg and yolov4.weight and put them into the darknet-master folder;
              9>put the avi file into the /data folder;
              10>change the path in ubuntu command to darknet-master;
              11>find Makefile in darnet-master and convert the value of OPENCV from 0 to 1; Then type in "make" in command line;
              12>run the following command:
                    "./darknet detector demo cfg/coco.data cfg/yolov4.cfg yolov4.weights data/test.avi"

